n- **Config Properties**:\n  - `policy.reprocess.scan-batch-size:100`\n  - `policy.reprocess.max-candidates-per-scan:1000`\n  - `policy.reprocess.rate-limit-per-second:100`\n  - `policy.reprocess.scan-lock-ttl-seconds:900`\n  - `policy.reprocess.scan-interval-ms:30000`\n\n**ReprocessState Enum**\n- Values: `NONE`, `INIT`, `RUNNING`, `SUCCESS`, `FAILED`\n- Used to track reprocess lifecycle\n\n---\n\n### 3. Entity Model & Type Structure\n\n**Entity Class**\n- **Path**: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/entity/Entity.java`\n- **Key Fields**:\n  - `Long id` - Entity ID\n  - `EntityType type` - Enum: HOST, USER_HOST_BINDING\n  - `String source` - e.g., \"PORTAL\"\n  - `String userId`, `hostId`, `adapterId` - Resource identifiers\n  - `String userIdentity`, `hostIdentity` - Composite identifiers\n  - `String processingStage` - Values: PENDING, LABELED, EVALUATED, ENFORCED\n  - `Integer processingCode` - 0 for success, non-zero for failure codes (31xx/32xx range)\n  - `String errorMessage` - Error details\n  - `String processingResult` - JSON with stage results (Lob)\n  - `boolean interrupted` - Can be set to stop processing\n  - `String attributeFingerprint` - For change detection\n  - `String lastReqVersion` - Request version tracking\n  - **`ReprocessState reprocessState`** - Default: NONE\n  - `Instant createdAt`, `updatedAt` - Timestamps\n\n---\n\n### 4. Endpoint Structure & Routing Patterns\n\n**Query Endpoint Pattern** (EntityController)\n- Request: `POST /api/v1/entities/query` with `EntityQueryDTO`\n- Request DTO:\n  ```java\n  - String stage (optional) - e.g., \"PENDING\"\n  - Integer code (optional) - processingCode to filter\n  - Integer pageNum (default: 1)\n  - Integer pageSize (default: 10)\n  - String sortKey (default: \"createdAt\") - Options: createdAt, processingStage, type\n  - String sortOrder (default: \"desc\") - Options: asc, desc\n  ```\n- Response: `ResultDTO<Pagination<Entity>>` with paged entities\n\n**Display Status Endpoint** (EntityController)\n- Request: `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status`\n- Response: `ResultDTO<EntityStateDisplayDTO>` with mapped display status\n- Status Mapping Logic (in EntityController):\n  - INIT → \"init\"\n  - RUNNING → \"running\"\n  - SUCCESS + ENFORCED + processingCode=0 → \"enforced\"\n  - SUCCESS + Other → \"failed\"\n  - FAILED → \"failed\"\n  - NONE → Derive from processingStage\n\n**Policy Apply Endpoint** (PolicyController)\n- Request: `POST /api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` (no body)\n- Response: `ResultDTO<MarkForReprocessResponse>`\n  ```java\n  - int markedCount\n  - int failedBatches\n  - int failedCount\n  - long timeCostMs\n  - String status (FAILED | PARTIAL_SUCCESS | SUCCESS)\n  - String message\n  ```\n\n**Error Response Pattern**\n- Wrapped in `ResultDTO<T>`:\n  ```java\n  - int code (0 for success, non-zero for errors)\n  - String errMsg (error message)\n  - T data (payload)\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Policy Processing Pipeline & Workflow\n\n**EntityStateMachine** (State Machine Driver)\n- **Path**: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/consumer/statemachine/EntityStateMachine.java`\n- **Method**: `public StatusOr<Entity> start(String requestId, boolean isAsync, Entity entity)`\n- **Stage Flow**:\n  1. PENDING → handlePending() → runLabel() → LABELED\n  2. LABELED → handleLabeled() → runPolicy() → EVALUATED\n  3. EVALUATED → handleEvaluated() → runEnforce() → ENFORCED\n  4. Each stage has MAX_RETRY = 3 attempts\n  5. If any stage fails (code != 0), processing stops and returns current state\n\n**PolicyService** (LABELED → EVALUATED stage)\n- **Path**: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/stages/PolicyService.java`\n- **Method**: `public ObjectNode evaluate(EntityDTO dto)`\n- **Returns**: ObjectNode with `code` and `data`\n- **Example**: Simple mock that adds policy decisions (allow VPN, rate limited)\n- **Success Code**: EntityProcessingCode.SUCCESS (0)\n- **Error Codes**: 31xx (temporary/retryable), 32xx (permanent)\n\n**Reprocess-Specific Pipeline** (PolicyReprocessJob)\n- Entity reprocess flow:\n  1. Reset: `processingStage = PENDING`, `processingCode = 0`, `processingResult = {}`, `interrupted = false`\n  2. Run state machine from PENDING (replays all stages)\n  3. Final state mapping:\n     - If state machine succeeds AND final stage = ENFORCED AND processingCode = 0 → `reprocessState = SUCCESS`\n     - Otherwise → `reprocessState = FAILED`\n\n**EntityRepository Custom Methods**\n- **Path**: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/repository/EntityRepository.java`\n- Key reprocess queries:\n  - `findTopNIdsNeedMarkForReprocess(Long lastId, ReprocessState targetState, Pageable)` - Scan entities to mark\n  - `markBatchForReprocess(List<Long> ids, ReprocessState targetState)` - Atomic batch update to INIT\n  - `findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, Pageable)` - Scan INIT entities for processing\n  - `claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id, Instant updatedAt)` - Atomic INIT → RUNNING transition\n  - `updateReprocessStateById(Long id, ReprocessState state, Instant updatedAt)` - Update final state\n  - `findProcessLockInfoById(Long id)` - Lightweight projection for lock validation\n\n---\n\n### 6. Entity Query & Display Status Integration\n\n**EntityStateDisplayDTO Response Structure**\n- **Path**: `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/dto/EntityStateDisplayDTO.java`\n- Fields:\n  - `Long id`\n  - `String type` - Entity type as string\n  - `String hostIdentity`, `userIdentity`\n  - `String processingStage` - Current stage\n  - `Integer processingCode` - Error code\n  - `Instant updatedAt` - Last update time\n  - `String displayStatus` - User-friendly status: \"init\", \"running\", \"enforced\", \"failed\"\n\n**Pagination Response**\n- **DTO**: `Pagination<T>` containing:\n  - `List<T> list` - Page contents\n  - `long totalRecords` - Total row count\n  - `int totalPages` - Number of pages\n  - `int pageNum` - Current page (1-indexed)\n  - `int pageSize` - Page size\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Location | Details |\n|---------|----------|---------|\n| **Transactional Safety** | EntityServiceImpl | Uses `PROPAGATION_REQUIRES_NEW` for independent batch commits |\n| **Distributed Locking** | PolicyReprocessJob | Global scan lock + entity-level process locks (Redis) |\n| **Atomic Claims** | EntityRepository | DB-level `WHERE reprocessState = 'INIT'` to prevent race conditions |\n| **Rate Limiting** | PolicyReprocessJob | Token bucket algorithm inside `ReprocessRateLimiter` |\n| **Metrics** | All services | Micrometer counters/timers/gauges for observability |\n| **Error Codes** | PolicyService | Success=0, Temporary=31xx, Permanent=32xx |\n| **Pagination** | EntityServiceImpl | Uses JPA Specification + PageRequest for flexible querying |\n| **State Reset** | PolicyReprocessJob.resetEntityProcessingState() | Clears processing fields to replay state machine |"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f740dd01-4690-4d22-a717-b6b57116b679","uuid":"a5d6c318-d9c2-4db9-a59e-c7a231ebae89","timestamp":"2026-04-20T08:26:47.518Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion to understand:\n1. Find EntityController and EntityService files — read them fully\n2. Find any existing \"reprocess\" or policy-related methods/patterns\n3. Understand the entity model/type structure\n4. Look for how other endpoints are structured (routing, request/response patterns)\n5. Check if there's a policy processing pipeline or workflow\n\nReport exact file paths, class/method signatures, and relevant patterns.","agentId":"a2b5359bbf2879ded","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Codebase